[[File:RioZoo3.jpg|250px|thumbnail|Monument to Macaco Tião in Rio de Janeiro's Zoo]] '''Macaco Tião''' ("Tião the Monkey") (January 16, 1963 in [[Rio de Janeiro]] – December 23, 1996 in Rio de Janeiro) was a [[chimpanzee]] of the Rio Janeiro Zoo who was very popular with children and visitors.<ref name="riozoo">{{cite web |url=http://rio.rj.gov.br/riozoo/tiao.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060506004446/http://rio.rj.gov.br/riozoo/tiao.htm |archivedate=2006-05-06 |title=Macaco Tião, 32 anos de preferência nacional |author=Rio Zoo}}</ref><ref name="estadão1994">{{cite web|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/ext/diariodopassado/20040116/000205438.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070310230616/http://www.estadao.com.br/ext/diariodopassado/20040116/000205438.htm|archivedate=2007-03-10|date=16 January 1994|accessdate=2016-03-10|title=Mau humorado, macaco Tião completa 31 anos|author=Estadão}}</ref><ref name="estadão2005">{{cite web|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/ultimas/cidades/noticias/2005/mar/18/75.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070310230746/http://www.estadao.com.br/ultimas/cidades/noticias/2005/mar/18/75.htm|archivedate=2007-03-10|date=18 March 2005|accessdate=2016-03-10|title=Zoológico do Rio completa 60 anos nesta sexta|author=Estadão}}</ref>
His name ("Tião") is in memory of Rio de Janeiro's [[patron saint]], [[Saint Sebastian|São Sebastião]]. He was {{convert|1.52|m|ftin}} tall and weighed {{convert|70|kg|lb}}.<ref name="riozoo"/>
==History== Tião started to become popular in the 1980s for his temperament, regarded as constant "bad mood" and having the habit of throwing mud and feces on the visitors of the zoo, especially politicians such as [[Marcello Alencar]].<ref name="estadão1994"/>
Tião became a celebrity in [[Brazil]], when in 1988, a magazine, ''[[Casseta Popular]]'', jokingly created his extra official candidature for mayor as a protest in defence of [[null vote|null voting]]. At the time, voting was written on papers instead of registered using [[Electronic voting|voting machines]]. It is estimated that more than 400,000 ballots were cast for him, and he reached third place in an election with 12 candidates. Because of that, he is now on the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as the most voted chimpanzee in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2008/11/081104.aspx|title=Most Votes For A Chimpazee|publisher=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=November 4, 2008|accessdate=2010-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100126014306/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2008/11/081104.aspx#|archive-date=2010-01-26|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> As Tião was not a registered candidate, all his ballots were considered as null. In 1996, the [[Elections in Brazil|voting system in Brazil]] was changed to electronic machines, so votes could no longer be cast for non-registered candidates.
Macaco Tião had always attracted enormous attention and had a special place in the zoo, built especially for him.<ref name="riozoo"/>
Nationally famous, lots of different Brazilian newspapers and the French ''[[Le Monde]]'' registered the news about his death,<ref name="riozoo"/> in December, 23 of 1996. Tião died of [[diabetes]] at the age of 34. The city of Rio de Janeiro declared official mourning of three days, with the flags of Rio de Janeiro's Zoo being flown at half-staff.<ref name="riozoo"/> His body was taken to the primate center of the state of Rio de Janeiro ([https://web.archive.org/web/20160405160523/http://www.inea.rj.gov.br/fma/centro-primatologia.asp Centro de Primatologia do Estado do Rio de Janeiro - CPRJ]), in the [[Guapimirim]] city, where his skeleton is preserved.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guapimirimonline.com/historia.php# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-07-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117050754/http://guapimirimonline.com/historia.php# |archive-date=2016-11-17 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
