The '''Popish Recusants Act 1592 ''' (35 Eliz. I, c. 2) was an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[Parliament of England]]. The Act forbade Roman Catholic [[recusancy|recusants]] from  moving more than five miles from their house or otherwise they would forfeit all their property.<ref>Dudley Julius Medley, ''A Student's Manual of English Constitutional History. Sixth Edition'' (Oxford: Basil Blackwell, 1925), p. 639.</ref>

