The '''Treaty of Bordeaux''' was a truce agreed to by King [[Henry III of England]] and King [[Louis IX of France]] on 27 April 1243, that ended the [[Saintonge War]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://doi.org/10.1093/ref:odnb/12950 |title=Henry III (1207–1272) |website=Oxford Dictionary of National Biography, online edition |publication-date=September 2010 |year=2004 |last=Ridgeway |first=Huw W. |accessdate=17 August 2013 |doi=10.1093/ref:odnb/12950 |publisher=Oxford University Press}}</ref> The truce did not stop the on-going clashes between the two countries led to further tensions later.
